description:
This is a 16 minute workout called 'Beginner Bodyweight Strength' from the channel Peter Donohoe.
The workout falls under Strength/Body weight.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Foundation Builder and The Comfort Moves vibe.
The The Foundation Builder vibe means Strengthen weak points, rebuild, perfect the basics. This is especially good for Those coming back from injury or refining fundamentals. The The Comfort Moves vibe means Safe, cozy, feel-good movement. This is especially good for Those who want to move but need it to feel easy and accessible..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light and Moderate.

Original workout description: Strengthen your lower body, core, and upper body with Pete and Aisyah during beginner-friendly, bodyweight exercises. ...
